Instructions for the MemTest86 floppy disk creation.
====================================================

1) Insert a floppy disk into the drive.
3) As root type: dd if=memtest86-<ver>.floppy.img of=<dev> 

where <dev> is the device the floppy drive is assigned to (eg. /dev/fd0 [Linux] or /dev/disk2 [Mac]).

Warning: all data on the floppy disk will be lost. 
Warning Warning: Make sure that the device used in the dd command above
is correct!!!
